Ed did not really teach very much to the class. As noted in the previous rating, Ed only lectured for 2 days. I did not come out learning much, other than how to soder wires together. I felt like I was in Kindergarden most of the time, bored, but having a good time.

Ed is a really nice guy who is interested in helping students learn. however, entering the class with as little knowledge of electronics as I did, you might have difficulty learning as he never really explains anything unless you ask a question (there were only two days of note-taking and that was it). Talk to him, he'll help you out, he's patient
